3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* bounce 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* bounce service client
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <bounce.h>
10/*
11/* int bounce_append(flags, id, stats, recipient, relay, dsn)
12/* int flags;
13/* const char *id;
14/* MSG_STATS *stats;
15/* RECIPIENT *rcpt;
16/* const char *relay;
17/* DSN *dsn;
18/*
19/* int bounce_flush(flags, queue, id, encoding, smtputf8, sender,
20/* dsn_envid, dsn_ret)
21/* int flags;
22/* const char *queue;
23/* const char *id;
24/* const char *encoding;
25/* int smtputf8;
26/* const char *sender;
27/* const char *dsn_envid;
28/* int dsn_ret;
29/*
30/* int bounce_flush_verp(flags, queue, id, encoding, smtputf8,
31/* sender, dsn_envid, dsn_ret, verp_delims)
32/* int flags;
33/* const char *queue;
34/* const char *id;
35/* const char *encoding;
36/* int smtputf8;
37/* const char *sender;
38/* const char *dsn_envid;
39/* int dsn_ret;
40/* const char *verp_delims;
41/*
42/* int bounce_one(flags, queue, id, encoding, smtputf8, sender,
43/* dsn_envid, ret, stats, recipient, relay, dsn)
44/* int flags;
45/* const char *queue;
46/* const char *id;
47/* const char *encoding;
48/* int smtputf8;
49/* const char *sender;
50/* const char *dsn_envid;
51/* int dsn_ret;
52/* MSG_STATS *stats;
53/* RECIPIENT *rcpt;
54/* const char *relay;
55/* DSN *dsn;
56/*
57/* void bounce_client_init(title, maps)
58/* const char *title;
59/* const char *maps;
60/* INTERNAL API
61/* DSN_FILTER *delivery_status_filter;
62/*
63/* int bounce_append_intern(flags, id, stats, recipient, relay, dsn)
64/* int flags;
65/* const char *id;
66/* MSG_STATS *stats;
67/* RECIPIENT *rcpt;
68/* const char *relay;
69/*
70/* int bounce_one_intern(flags, queue, id, encoding, smtputf8, sender,
71/* dsn_envid, ret, stats, recipient, relay, dsn)
72/* int flags;
73/* const char *queue;
74/* const char *id;
75/* const char *encoding;
76/* int smtputf8;
77/* const char *sender;
78/* const char *dsn_envid;
79/* int dsn_ret;
80/* MSG_STATS *stats;
81/* RECIPIENT *rcpt;
82/* const char *relay;
83/* DSN *dsn;
84/* DESCRIPTION
85/* This module implements the client interface to the message
86/* bounce service, which maintains a per-message log of status
87/* records with recipients that were bounced, and the dsn_text why.
88/*
89/* bounce_append() appends a dsn_text for non-delivery to the
90/* bounce log for the named recipient, updates the address
91/* verification service, or updates a message delivery record
92/* on request by the sender. The flags argument determines
93/* the action.
94/*
95/* bounce_flush() actually bounces the specified message to
96/* the specified sender, including the bounce log that was
97/* built with bounce_append(). The bounce logfile is removed
98/* upon successful completion.
99/*
100/* bounce_flush_verp() is like bounce_flush(), but sends one
101/* notification per recipient, with the failed recipient encoded
102/* into the sender address.
103/*
104/* bounce_one() bounces one recipient and immediately sends a
105/* notification to the sender. This procedure does not append
106/* the recipient and dsn_text to the per-message bounce log, and
107/* should be used when a delivery agent changes the error
108/* return address in a manner that depends on the recipient
109/* address.
110/*
111/* bounce_client_init() initializes an optional DSN filter.
112/*
113/* bounce_append_intern() and bounce_one_intern() are for use
114/* after the DSN filter.
115/*
116/* Arguments:
117/* .IP flags
118/* The bitwise OR of zero or more of the following (specify
119/* BOUNCE_FLAG_NONE to request no special processing):
120/* .RS
121/* .IP BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN
122/* Delete the bounce log in case of an error (as in: pretend
123/* that we never even tried to bounce this message).
124/* .IP BOUNCE_FLAG_DELRCPT
125/* When specified with a flush request, request that
126/* recipients be deleted from the queue file.
127/*
128/* Note: the bounce daemon ignores this request when the
129/* recipient queue file offset is <= 0.
130/* .IP DEL_REQ_FLAG_MTA_VRFY
131/* The message is an MTA-requested address verification probe.
132/* Update the address verification database instead of bouncing
133/* mail.
134/* .IP DEL_REQ_FLAG_USR_VRFY
135/* The message is a user-requested address expansion probe.
136/* Update the message delivery record instead of bouncing mail.
137/* .IP DEL_REQ_FLAG_RECORD
138/* This is a normal message with logged delivery. Update the
139/* message delivery record and bounce the mail.
140/* .RE
141/* .IP queue
142/* The message queue name of the original message file.
143/* .IP id
144/* The message queue id if the original message file. The bounce log
145/* file has the same name as the original message file.
146/* .IP stats
147/* Time stamps from different message delivery stages
148/* and session reuse count.
149/* .IP rcpt
150/* Recipient information. See recipient_list(3).
151/* .IP relay
152/* Name of the host that the message could not be delivered to.
153/* This information is used for syslogging only.
154/* .IP encoding
155/* The body content encoding: MAIL_ATTR_ENC_{7BIT,8BIT,NONE}.
156/* .IP smtputf8
157/* The level of SMTPUTF8 support (to be defined).
158/* .IP sender
159/* The sender envelope address.
160/* .IP dsn_envid
161/* Optional DSN envelope ID.
162/* .IP dsn_ret
163/* Optional DSN return full/headers option.
164/* .IP dsn
165/* Delivery status. See dsn(3). The specified action is ignored.
166/* .IP verp_delims
167/* VERP delimiter characters, used when encoding the failed
168/* sender into the envelope sender address.
169/* DIAGNOSTICS
170/* In case of success, these functions log the action, and return a
171/* zero value. Otherwise, the functions return a non-zero result,
172/* and when BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN is disabled, log that message
173/* delivery is deferred.
174/* .IP title
175/* The origin of the optional DSN filter lookup table names.
176/* .IP maps
177/* The optional "type:table" DSN filter lookup table names,
178/* separated by comma or whitespace.
179/* BUGS
180/* Should be replaced by routines with an attribute-value based
181/* interface instead of an interface that uses a rigid argument list.
182/* LICENSE
183/* .ad
184/* .fi
185/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
186/* AUTHOR(S)
187/* Wietse Venema
188/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
189/* P.O. Box 704
190/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
191/*--*/
192

204/* Global library. */

206#define DSN_INTERN
207#include <mail_params.h>
208#include <mail_proto.h>
209#include <log_adhoc.h>
210#include <dsn_util.h>
211#include <rcpt_print.h>
212#include <dsn_print.h>
213#include <verify.h>
214#include <defer.h>
215#include <trace.h>
216#include <bounce.h>
217
218/* Shared internally, between bounce and defer clients. */
219
220DSN_FILTER *delivery_status_filter;
221
222/* bounce_append - append delivery status to per-message bounce log */
223
224int bounce_append(int flags, const char *id, MSG_STATS *stats,
225 RECIPIENT *rcpt, const char *relay,
226 DSN *dsn)
227{
228 DSN my_dsn = *dsn;
229 DSN *dsn_res;
230
231 /*
232 * Sanity check. If we're really confident, change this into msg_panic
233 * (remember, this information may be under control by a hostile server).
234 */
235 if (my_dsn.status[0] != '5' || !dsn_valid(my_dsn.status)) {
236 msg_warn("bounce_append: ignoring dsn code \"%s\"", my_dsn.status);
237 my_dsn.status = "5.0.0";
238 }
239
240 /*
241 * DSN filter (Postfix 3.0).
242 */
243 if (delivery_status_filter != 0
244 && (dsn_res = dsn_filter_lookup(delivery_status_filter, &my_dsn)) != 0) {
245 if (dsn_res->status[0] == '4')
246 return (defer_append_intern(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, dsn_res));
247 my_dsn = *dsn_res;
248 }
249 return (bounce_append_intern(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn));
250}
251
252/* bounce_append_intern - append delivery status to per-message bounce log */
253
254int bounce_append_intern(int flags, const char *id, MSG_STATS *stats,
255 RECIPIENT *rcpt, const char *relay,
256 DSN *dsn)
257{
258 DSN my_dsn = *dsn;
259 int status;
260
261 /*
262 * MTA-requested address verification information is stored in the verify
263 * service database.
264 */
265 if (flags & DEL_REQ_FLAG_MTA_VRFY) {
266 my_dsn.action = "undeliverable";
267 status = verify_append(id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn,
268 DEL_RCPT_STAT_BOUNCE);
269 return (status);
270 }
271
272 /*
273 * User-requested address verification information is logged and mailed
274 * to the requesting user.
275 */
276 if (flags & DEL_REQ_FLAG_USR_VRFY) {
277 my_dsn.action = "undeliverable";
278 status = trace_append(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn);
279 return (status);
280 }
281
282 /*
283 * Normal (well almost) delivery. When we're pretending that we can't
284 * bounce, don't create a defer log file when we wouldn't keep the bounce
285 * log file. That's a lot of negatives in one sentence.
286 */
287 else if (var_soft_bounce && (flags & BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN)) {
288 return (-1);
289 }
290
291 /*
292 * Normal mail delivery. May also send a delivery record to the user.
293 *
294 * XXX DSN We write all recipients to the bounce logfile regardless of DSN
295 * NOTIFY options, because those options don't apply to postmaster
296 * notifications.
297 */
298 else {
299 char *my_status = mystrdup(my_dsn.status);
300 const char *log_status = var_soft_bounce ? "SOFTBOUNCE" : "bounced";
301
302 /*
303 * Supply default action.
304 */
305 my_dsn.status = my_status;
306 if (var_soft_bounce) {
307 my_status[0] = '4';
308 my_dsn.action = "delayed";
309 } else {
310 my_dsn.action = "failed";
311 }
312
313 if (mail_command_client(MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE, var_soft_bounce ?
314 var_defer_service : var_bounce_service,
315 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_NREQ, BOUNCE_CMD_APPEND),
316 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, flags),
317 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUEID, id),
318 SEND_ATTR_FUNC(rcpt_print, (void *) rcpt),
319 SEND_ATTR_FUNC(dsn_print, (void *) &my_dsn),
320 ATTR_TYPE_END) == 0
321 && ((flags & DEL_REQ_FLAG_RECORD) == 0
322 || trace_append(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay,
323 &my_dsn) == 0)) {
324 log_adhoc(id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn, log_status);
325 status = (var_soft_bounce ? -1 : 0);
326 } else if ((flags & BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN) == 0) {
327 VSTRING *junk = vstring_alloc(100);
328
329 my_dsn.status = "4.3.0";
330 vstring_sprintf(junk, "%s or %s service failure",
331 var_bounce_service, var_trace_service);
332 my_dsn.reason = vstring_str(junk);
333 status = defer_append_intern(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn);
334 vstring_free(junk);
335 } else {
336 status = -1;
337 }
338 myfree(my_status);
339 return (status);
340 }
341}
342
343/* bounce_flush - flush the bounce log and deliver to the sender */
344
345int bounce_flush(int flags, const char *queue, const char *id,
346 const char *encoding, int smtputf8,
347 const char *sender, const char *dsn_envid,
348 int dsn_ret)
349{
350
351 /*
352 * When we're pretending that we can't bounce, don't send a bounce
353 * message.
354 */
355 if (var_soft_bounce)
356 return (-1);
357 if (mail_command_client(MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE, var_bounce_service,
358 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_NREQ, BOUNCE_CMD_FLUSH),
359 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, flags),
360 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUE, queue),
361 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUEID, id),
362 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_ENCODING, encoding),
363 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_SMTPUTF8, smtputf8),
364 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_SENDER, sender),
365 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_DSN_ENVID, dsn_envid),
366 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_DSN_RET, dsn_ret),
367 ATTR_TYPE_END) == 0) {
368 return (0);
369 } else if ((flags & BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN) == 0) {
370 msg_info("%s: status=deferred (bounce failed)", id);
371 return (-1);
372 } else {
373 return (-1);
374 }
375}

377/* bounce_flush_verp - verpified notification */
378
379int bounce_flush_verp(int flags, const char *queue, const char *id,
380 const char *encoding, int smtputf8,
381 const char *sender, const char *dsn_envid,
382 int dsn_ret, const char *verp_delims)
383{
384
385 /*
386 * When we're pretending that we can't bounce, don't send a bounce
387 * message.
388 */
389 if (var_soft_bounce)
390 return (-1);
391 if (mail_command_client(MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE, var_bounce_service,
392 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_NREQ, BOUNCE_CMD_VERP),
393 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, flags),
394 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUE, queue),
395 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUEID, id),
396 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_ENCODING, encoding),
397 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_SMTPUTF8, smtputf8),
398 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_SENDER, sender),
399 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_DSN_ENVID, dsn_envid),
400 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_DSN_RET, dsn_ret),
401 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_VERPDL, verp_delims),
402 ATTR_TYPE_END) == 0) {
403 return (0);
404 } else if ((flags & BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN) == 0) {
405 msg_info("%s: status=deferred (bounce failed)", id);
406 return (-1);
407 } else {
408 return (-1);
409 }
410}

412/* bounce_one - send notice for one recipient */
413
414int bounce_one(int flags, const char *queue, const char *id,
415 const char *encoding, int smtputf8,
416 const char *sender, const char *dsn_envid,
417 int dsn_ret, MSG_STATS *stats, RECIPIENT *rcpt,
418 const char *relay, DSN *dsn)
419{
420 DSN my_dsn = *dsn;
421 DSN *dsn_res;
422
423 /*
424 * Sanity check.
425 */
426 if (my_dsn.status[0] != '5' || !dsn_valid(my_dsn.status)) {
427 msg_warn("bounce_one: ignoring dsn code \"%s\"", my_dsn.status);
428 my_dsn.status = "5.0.0";
429 }
430
431 /*
432 * DSN filter (Postfix 3.0).
433 */
434 if (delivery_status_filter != 0
435 && (dsn_res = dsn_filter_lookup(delivery_status_filter, &my_dsn)) != 0) {
436 if (dsn_res->status[0] == '4')
437 return (defer_append_intern(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, dsn_res));
438 my_dsn = *dsn_res;
439 }
440 return (bounce_one_intern(flags, queue, id, encoding, smtputf8, sender,
441 dsn_envid, dsn_ret, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn));
442}
443
444/* bounce_one_intern - send notice for one recipient */
445
446int bounce_one_intern(int flags, const char *queue, const char *id,
447 const char *encoding, int smtputf8,
448 const char *sender, const char *dsn_envid,
449 int dsn_ret, MSG_STATS *stats,
450 RECIPIENT *rcpt, const char *relay,
451 DSN *dsn)
452{
453 DSN my_dsn = *dsn;
454 int status;
455
456 /*
457 * MTA-requested address verification information is stored in the verify
458 * service database.
459 */
460 if (flags & DEL_REQ_FLAG_MTA_VRFY) {
461 my_dsn.action = "undeliverable";
462 status = verify_append(id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn,
463 DEL_RCPT_STAT_BOUNCE);
464 return (status);
465 }
466
467 /*
468 * User-requested address verification information is logged and mailed
469 * to the requesting user.
470 */
471 if (flags & DEL_REQ_FLAG_USR_VRFY) {
472 my_dsn.action = "undeliverable";
473 status = trace_append(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn);
474 return (status);
475 }
476
477 /*
478 * When we're not bouncing, then use the standard multi-recipient logfile
479 * based procedure.
480 */
481 else if (var_soft_bounce) {
482 return (bounce_append_intern(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn));
483 }
484
485 /*
486 * Normal mail delivery. May also send a delivery record to the user.
487 *
488 * XXX DSN We send all recipients regardless of DSN NOTIFY options, because
489 * those options don't apply to postmaster notifications.
490 */
491 else {
492
493 /*
494 * Supply default action.
495 */
496 my_dsn.action = "failed";
497
498 if (mail_command_client(MAIL_CLASS_PRIVATE, var_bounce_service,
499 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_NREQ, BOUNCE_CMD_ONE),
500 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, flags),
501 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUE, queue),
502 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUEID, id),
503 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_ENCODING, encoding),
504 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_SMTPUTF8, smtputf8),
505 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_SENDER, sender),
506 SEND_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_DSN_ENVID, dsn_envid),
507 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_DSN_RET, dsn_ret),
508 SEND_ATTR_FUNC(rcpt_print, (void *) rcpt),
509 SEND_ATTR_FUNC(dsn_print, (void *) &my_dsn),
510 ATTR_TYPE_END) == 0
511 && ((flags & DEL_REQ_FLAG_RECORD) == 0
512 || trace_append(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay,
513 &my_dsn) == 0)) {
514 log_adhoc(id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn, "bounced");
515 status = 0;
516 } else if ((flags & BOUNCE_FLAG_CLEAN) == 0) {
517 VSTRING *junk = vstring_alloc(100);
518
519 my_dsn.status = "4.3.0";
520 vstring_sprintf(junk, "%s or %s service failure",
521 var_bounce_service, var_trace_service);
522 my_dsn.reason = vstring_str(junk);
523 status = defer_append_intern(flags, id, stats, rcpt, relay, &my_dsn);
524 vstring_free(junk);
525 } else {
526 status = -1;
527 }
528 return (status);
529 }
530}
531
532/* bounce_client_init - initialize bounce/defer DSN filter */
533
534void bounce_client_init(const char *title, const char *maps)
535{
536 static const char myname[] = "bounce_client_init";
537
538 if (delivery_status_filter != 0)
539 msg_panic("%s: duplicate initialization", myname);
540 if (*maps)
541 delivery_status_filter = dsn_filter_create(title, maps);
542}
